<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Emergency Hotlines | Navigator +</title>
    <%- include('partials/styles.ejs') %>
    <style>
        body { padding-top: 86px; }
        .hotline-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius-panel); padding: 24px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(15,42,30,0.07); height: 100%; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
        .hotline-num { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 800; font-size: 32px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--brand-red-dark), var(--brand-red)); -webkit-background-clip: text; background-clip: text; color: transparent; }
        .hotline-card.urgent { border: 2px solid var(--brand-red); }
        .steps-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius-panel); padding: 28px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(15,42,30,0.07); }
        .steps-card ol { padding-left: 20px; }
        .steps-card li { margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--ink-muted); }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs', { page: 'hotlines' }) %>

    <div class="page-hero page-hero-urgent text-center">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="display-6">Emergency Hotlines</h1>
            <p class="mx-auto">Know these numbers before you need them. A calm, correct call can save a life.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mt-4 mb-5">

        <%- include('partials/readAloud.ejs') %>

        <div id="readable-content">
        <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card urgent">
                    <div class="hotline-num">999</div>
                    <h6>Police Emergency</h6>
                    <p>For crimes, road accidents involving injury, or any life-threatening situation requiring police response.</p>
                    <p class="mb-0"><small>Can't call safely? SMS <strong>71999</strong> instead.</small></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card urgent">
                    <div class="hotline-num">995</div>
                    <h6>SCDF Ambulance / Fire</h6>
                    <p>For life-threatening medical emergencies and fire incidents, including serious road accident injuries. Free from mobile and landline phones.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card">
                    <div class="hotline-num">6547 0000</div>
                    <h6>Traffic Police Information Hotline</h6>
                    <p>For reporting traffic-related matters and non-emergency accident enquiries.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card">
                    <div class="hotline-num">1800&#8209;255&#8209;0000</div>
                    <h6>Non-Emergency Police Hotline</h6>
                    <p>For non-urgent police matters that don't require an immediate 999 response.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card">
                    <div class="hotline-num">6262 6262</div>
                    <h6>NurseFirst Helpline</h6>
                    <p>For medical advice on non-emergency conditions and guidance on where to seek appropriate care.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="hotline-card">
                    <div class="hotline-num">1800 202 6868</div>
                    <h6>National Care Hotline</h6>
                    <p>For emotional support if a road accident — yours or someone else's — has left you shaken or distressed.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="steps-card mb-4">
            <h5>📍 If you witness or are involved in a road accident</h5>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Check for danger first.</strong> Move to a safe spot away from moving traffic before doing anything else.</li>
                <li><strong>Call for help.</strong> Dial 999 if anyone is injured or it's a serious collision; dial 995 if someone needs urgent medical attention.</li>
                <li><strong>Give clear information</strong> — your location (street name, nearest landmark or postal code), what happened, and how many people are hurt.</li>
                <li><strong>Stay on the line</strong> while responders gather details, and don't hang up until you're told to.</li>
                <li><strong>Don't move injured persons</strong> unless they're in immediate danger — wait for trained responders.</li>
                <li><strong>Report within 24 hours</strong> to the police if you're a driver involved in an accident, so an official report is on record.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: Singapore Civil Defence Force; Singapore Police Force public guidance</p>
        </div>

        <div class="alert-caution">
            <strong>Please use emergency numbers responsibly.</strong> Misusing 995 or 999 for non-emergencies can delay help reaching someone who genuinely needs it — and may result in a penalty.
        </div>
        </div><!-- /#readable-content -->

    </div>

    <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>
